text: Stanislaw Wojciechowski (15 March 1869 – 9 April 1953) was a Polish politician and scholar who served as President of Poland from 1922 to 1926. He became president after his predecessor, Gabriel Narutowicz, was assassinated. == References == Category:1869 births Category:1953 deaths Category:Presidents of Poland Category:Polish politicians
title: Stanisław Wojciechowski
